{"questionId":"3430592","questionHtml":"<p>Two samples of a gas are kept in separate containers. The molecules of each sample have the same average translational speed, but the samples have a different density.</p>\n<p>What is correct about the pressure and the temperature of the samples, as compared to each other?</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<table style=\"width:342px;\" border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height:22px;\">\n<td style=\"width:47px;height:22px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width:141.203px;text-align:center;height:22px;\"><strong>Pressure</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width:156.797px;text-align:center;height:22px;\"><strong>Temperature</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:20px;\">\n<td style=\"width:47px;height:20px;\">&nbsp;A.</td>\n<td style=\"width:141.203px;text-align:center;height:20px;\">same</td>\n<td style=\"width:156.797px;text-align:center;height:20px;\">same</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:20px;\">\n<td style=\"width:47px;height:20px;\">&nbsp;B.</td>\n<td style=\"width:141.203px;text-align:center;height:20px;\">same</td>\n<td style=\"width:156.797px;text-align:center;height:20px;\">different</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:22px;\">\n<td style=\"width:47px;height:22px;\">&nbsp;C.</td>\n<td style=\"width:141.203px;text-align:center;height:22px;\">different</td>\n<td style=\"width:156.797px;text-align:center;height:22px;\">same</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:21px;\">\n<td style=\"width:47px;height:21px;\">&nbsp;D.</td>\n<td style=\"width:141.203px;text-align:center;height:21px;\">different</td>\n<td style=\"width:156.797px;text-align:center;height:21px;\">different</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>","markschemeHtml":"<p>C</p>","meta":{"questionId":"3430592","referenceCode":"EXE.1A.SL.TZ0.9","subjectId":"59-dp-physics-first-assessment-2025","title":"Two samples of a gas are kept in separate containers. The molecules of each sample have the same average translational speed, but the samples have a different density. What is corr","paper":"1A","level":"SL","